Protect demo-critical flows.

Demo-critical flows:

- startup via `./start.sh`;
- shutdown via `./stop.sh`;
- templates list/create/edit/delete;
- editor save/reload;
- control TAKE/CLEAR/UPDATE;
- browser renderer;
- settings/channels;
- rundowns;
- uploads;
- LLM fallback;
- DeckLink best-effort behavior.

Rules:

- Do not change default ports without explicit request.
- Do not break `./start.sh` or `./stop.sh`.
- Do not change WebSocket command behavior without checking control and renderer.
- Do not remove browser renderer fallback.
- Do not make LLM or DeckLink mandatory for normal app usage.
- Do not hide startup failures.
- Keep error messages actionable for demo operators.

After touching demo-critical code, run or ask to run:

- `npm run typecheck`
- `npm run build`
- `./start.sh`
- relevant manual scenario from `docs/baseline-checklist.md`
